    "type": "Requirement",
    "name": "FDA Class II CPB hemolysis computational prediction requirement",
    "description": "Per FDA guidance on computational fluid dynamics for blood-contacting devices, a Class II CPB pump submission must demonstrate that computational hemolysis predictions bound or match experimental hemolysis measurements. The relative hemolysis index RH must be less than 1.0 when comparing device under test to predicate. This requirement governs the acceptance criterion for the Morrison COU1 CFD hemolysis assessment at Model Risk Level 2.",
    "source": "FDA Guidance: Reporting of Computational Modeling Studies in Medical Device Submissions (2016)",
    "regulatoryBasis": "21 CFR Part 870 — Cardiovascular Devices"
  },
