      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented with sufficient fidelity to enable meaningful comparison with CFD boundary conditions, including fluid properties, operating speeds, and flow rates.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump experimental data from Hariharan et al. (2011) provides fully documented test conditions: blood analog fluid (60% glycerin/water, viscosity 3.5 cP), five operating points (2.5–7 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM), temperature-controlled environment. CFD boundary conditions matched to within measurement uncertainty bounds."
