      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI used in validation (NIH) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint (hemolysis risk) and the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1).",
      "rationale": "Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH) is the standard regulatory QoI for blood pump hemolysis assessment per FDA and ISO 10993-4. RH directly compares device NIH to predicate device NIH, providing the regulatory decision variable. QoI relevance is high — no transformation or surrogate relationship required between validation QoI and COU decision criterion."
    },
    {
