    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 requirements for Class II CPB devices. Validation evidence from FDA generic pump benchmark demonstrates CFD predictions bound experimental hemolysis measurements (RH < 1.0) at all five operating conditions. Discretization error quantified at 3.2% GCI — below 5% acceptance threshold. Overall credibility assessment supports use of CFD model to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Decision: Accepted for regulatory submission.",
